rComments: Super strict on the online system, nit picky over systems that could have been done to make procedures a lot less stressful for students. Lots of reading, reads off slides, but did make an effort to make lectures a bit more enjoyable.

You have to use an online textbook, on top of spending hours reading the textbook ( you have to do it because there are quizzes and questions that are marked for participation), there is then a 3-hour lecture which you need to attend if you want MORE participation marks. The class itself is interesting but a lot of work.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: She is a fairly new professor and I could tell that she was very organized and prepared which I appreciated. I just felt that her lectures lacked a real interest in the content so I had a hard time engaging in it myself. Also, there were a lot of textbook readings. Overall though, she was friendly and her course expectations were made clear.
